,"Portuguese (<b>Constâncio</b>) and Spanish: from local equivalents of the Latin personal name <i>Constantius</i> (see   Constant  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Constant","meanings":["Medieval form of the Late Latin name <i>Constans</i> ‘steadfast’ (genitive <i>Constantis</i>). This was not a common name in the Middle Ages, but was used particularly in the Maude family. The vernacular variant  <b>Costin</b>  is also found. The name was taken up more widely among Christians from the 17th century onwards, partly because of its transparent meaning and partly as expressing a determination to follow the exhortations of  St Peter : ‘Be sober, be vigilant; because your adversary the devil, as a roaring lion, walketh about, seeking whom he may devour; whom resist stedfast (<i>constant</i>) in the faith’ (1 Peter 5:8–9)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Constancia was born in 1240, in Somerton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Sir Thomas de Gardinis. She died in 1331, at the age of 91."},"et":{"1240–1331":"1240–1331","1253–1328":"1253–1328","1277–Male":"1277–Surnud","1279–1328":"1279–1328","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","before 7 June 1328":"15. juuni 1328","1331":"1331","1253":"1253","1240":"1240","1328":"1328","Somerton, Cherwell, Oxfordshire, England":"Somerton, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ixning,Suffolk,England":"Exning, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somerton, Oxford, England, Great Britain":"Somerton, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1240–1331":"1240–1331","1253–1328":"1253–1328","1277–Male":"1277–Kuollut","1279–1328":"1279–1328","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","before 7 June 1328":"15. kesäkuuta 1328","1331":"1331","1253":"1253","1240":"1240","1328":"1328","Somerton, Cherwell, Oxfordshire, England":"Somerton, Oxfordshire, Eng